<br>
Logging in Wythe again last night and getting her to 23 (wow I do like the experience bonus :P) was a blast...but also a shock. When I stopped playing Wythe I made 7 bluebie twinks. Playing an untwinked bard again took some adjustments. It's funny how you forget the times a pgt was a good weapon so quickly...<br>
<br>
But there is something oddly addictive about Sullon. I don't think its the people exactly, sure they are all nice enough in their own ways, but no one is There to be nice. What I find most interesting is the way Norrath itself is a brave new world. Porting into GFay becomes scary, DL more so. It's like the world has shadows and monsters lurking in them that aren't on the spawn table, strange things that you've never seen before. Real threats and real dangers.<br>
<br>
The high end game is fun enough. I can't see it being more so on a red server. Since so much of it involves time, adding to that time just seems like adding to the annoyancesf. Erasing the need for it though, which I think SZ does by offering a counter to lfg in seb chardok and velks, another way to pass the time, is Very interesting. I don't think I have time to play really, and I am quite fond of my life on Saryrn, but still, I am sort of glad I made Wythe way back when, and every once in a while I can dust her off and go exploring.<br>
<br>
As somone (I forget and never knew who) used to say, &quot;there is no love on Sullon Zek&quot;. However sometimes that can be totally entertaining. <p><a href="www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87982">Vainne</a> K'harmicdeva
