60th Sorcerer - Sullon Zek<BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvid187lestat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vid187lestat</A> at: 5/9/02 1:09:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uulynvindix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulyn Vindix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/9/02 1:31:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=703.topic&index=67>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SZek</span><hr size=1> Sullon Zek is the best server, in spite of all of its problems.  It has 2 same-team twink slots now if that's an inducement for some people who just have to have toys to play with.<br>
<br>
The no rules, no level limit environment eventually becomes second nature to you, and playing on the old Zeks gets very frustrating - certain types of griefing behavior quite _depend_ on the other server's level limit, namely super-twinked lowbie ganking on RZ to steal more twink gear, or just deleveled newbie harrassment on the other Zeks.  On SZ you can only grief newbies but any red that happens to pass through can attack you.  Granted, people still sometimes go into greenie zones and make like lawnmowers, but that's life.<br>
<br>
PVP an afterthought, btw Vermillion?  PVP is the only thing that makes EQ more than (sorry) a chat-room with a shot-up RPG with poorly written content tacked on.  On a blue server you level and get gear so that you can level more and get more gear, so you can get to raids, where you can get more gear, that will let you level to let you raid to get more gear.<br>
<br>
On SZ you do that so you can kill and not be killed with better gear and more levels.  EQ's a bit more interesting with random, zoning, superintelligent levl 60 opponents, wouldn't you say?  Continue to play against map-designers and genius mob AI if you find that challenging, however.  Noone will stop you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
