<br>
Yeah, we want more people, but we don't want any of the people that are like &quot;well, I like killing computer AI, but it kinda sucks that someone might kill me and make it take longer for me to kill computer AI&quot;.  Please don't sign up.<br>
<br>
Yup, there are some people on Evil and Newt team  who do play purely because the uber mobs are less contested for than on their old servers.  Most of the people are here because they *want* to fight other people, its fun to get in a battle over a zone or to recover a corpse or just because you happened to be passing through a zone.  Most of us get gear because being rooted sucks, and more hp means you'll have a better chance.  Loot is NOT an end-all.  Yeah, I wanna look secksay and have nice big green numbers on my stat list, but thats just so I can kick your butt better (or die less often)<br>
<br>
I think the original post was for all those people that started SZ the first couple of weeks, and then left because there were just so many of us.  If you love to play a &quot;co-operative game&quot; thats great, enjoy your blue server.  However, if you wanna get the chance to kick some butt, and pvp with the best pvpers around, Sullon Zek just might be for you.<br>
<br>
Evil and Newt teams are very viable. They are closer than ever in power now thanks to most of &lt;ruin&gt; leaving for dungeon seige and a lot of newts returning twinked from legends.  Good team still has it hard, but an old evil guild just rerolled good, and goods are gaining pve experience every day.  Sullon Zek isn't for everyone, and thats ok, but if you are interest come on over =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uquindinarolorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quindinar Olorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/15/02 1:49:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=703.topic&index=74>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Damn, I'm sold.  Creating a character tonight.  I have a lot invested on Tarew Marr, but this sounds like a nice change every once in awhile. <p><BR>
