<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   The high end game is fun enough. I can't see it being more so on a red server. Since so much of it involves time, adding to that time just seems like adding to the annoyancesf. Erasing the need for it though, which I think SZ does by offering a counter to lfg in seb chardok and velks, another way to pass the time, is Very interesting. I don't think I have time to play really, and I am quite fond of my life on Saryrn, but still, I am sort of glad I made Wythe way back when, and every once in a while I can dust her off and go exploring. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well about the high end game and &quot;time&quot;.<br>
Alot of epic battles (50+ people) and smaller skirmishes have <br>
occured mostly in and around :<br>
Kael, WL, Skyshrine, CS/SG, Western Wastes, ToV/DN.<br>
Usually over key dragons and other things.<br>
<br>
<br>
So when you said it takes so much &quot;time&quot; to do high end<br>
stuff.<br>
<br>
Well on SZ, as soon as you gather more than about<br>
12 people, the timer is ticking until the enemy hears<br>
about it and decides to attack with PvP or a train or<br>
whatever to disrupt your team. So you have to move<br>
relatively quickly and be mobile and flexible or you<br>
can get crushed. In some ways that makes things go<br>
faster and people work better under some pressure.<br>
It changes group strategy too, like putting an evac in<br>
every group in case of a train from the enemy.<br>
<br>
And there are also fights over the few good places to<br>
level up at lvl 55-60.  Places like Velketors especially.<br>
Sebilis being so remote has remained Evil controlled<br>
generally.  Goods control The Hole, while Neutrals control<br>
Velketors generally.  Other dungeons are up for grabs.<br>
Sometimes you have to fight/defend or clear out a dungeon<br>
to have a chance at xp/loot from there. It can add an<br>
interesting dynamic and can be frustrating too so a <br>
certain attitude about these things is required. <br>
<br>
<br>
Try it out, you'll like the added dimensions to the gameplay,<br>
especially if you are burnt out on normal EQ.<br>
<br>
