<br>
PvP servers offer so much more to do compared to blue servers.  Logging on my Rogue lately is becoming painful, unless the &quot;core&quot; of my guild is on, in which case I go to the Hole or something with them, which is making me edge over to SZ permanently.  <br>
<br>
On SZ, there is actual risk wherever you are, you have to constantly /who, always look around.  Also, the small amount of people results in the fact that everyone is known, which is pretty cool.<br>
<br>
Again, in my opinion, it is all that great, and even more.  It's some of the most fun I've had in EQ ever, and to anyone considering it, do give it a whirl, it is way worth it.<br>
